05:07.080 --> 05:09.280
<i>to independently
investigate and prosecute</i>

05:09.316 --> 05:11.481
<i>cases of extreme
negligence or bias.</i>

05:11.516 --> 05:14.751
<i>But to date, St. Louis has
only adopted two laws</i>

05:14.786 --> 05:16.320
<i>that apply to those
proposed policies.</i>

05:16.355 --> 05:18.121
<i>We met up with the police chief</i>

05:18.157 --> 05:19.997
<i>of the St. Louis Metropolitan
Police Department</i>

05:20.025 --> 05:22.759
<i>to find out why reforms
are so slow.</i>

05:23.896 --> 05:26.263
One of the outgrowths
of the Ferguson protests

05:26.298 --> 05:27.764
was this group called
Campaign Zero.

05:27.799 --> 05:29.866
And we looked
at some of the--

05:29.901 --> 05:32.701
it's a 10-point
policy platform--

05:32.737 --> 05:36.472
independent investigations into
police shootings, body cams.

05:36.507 --> 05:40.209
Why is it so difficult
to get these policy solutions

05:40.245 --> 05:42.745
actually utilized
by police forces?

05:42.780 --> 05:45.613
Here's the balance. That group doesn't
represent the entire community.

05:45.648 --> 05:48.984
There are people that want us to
do more aggressive-style policing.

05:49.019 --> 05:51.619
There are people
that want us to...

05:51.654 --> 05:54.489
do more stop-and-frisk,
if you will, just as an example.

05:54.524 --> 05:57.392
And it's law enforcement's job,
it's the police chief's job,

05:57.427 --> 06:00.295
to find the balance in their
community between those.

06:00.330 --> 06:02.363
